The paper deals with image recognition, specifically fine-grained object recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a novel approach to exploit relationships among object classes, which involves modeling bipartite-graph labels and optimizing through back-propagation, indicating a focus on machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of a new food benchmark dataset, which suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) subfields.
